Change setup.py to include circleci template

Switch to using HTTPS for cloning of repositories

Handle sub-directories

This adds better support for executing commands from "somwhere" inside
the repository, before you had to run them in the top directory.

This adds support for assignments having the same file name, previously
the rendered notebooks would have the same name and overwrite each
other.
Working towards a autograder with points

Add graceful handling of a student not existing

When distributing work a student's repository can not (yet) exist and we
need to give a nice error message in that case.

Close outstanding PRs whe ndistributing new material

When we distribute new material to students close outstanding PRs that
were delivering new material as we will only end up with merge conflicts
if students try to merge these old PRs once we have made a new one.
Move when we close PRs to a later moment to reduce churn
Ask user for input on message for distributing material
Fix path handling when running notebooks
Extend CircleCI config to support conda files
Add handling of the case when the template repo exists
Fix init fun to check for token before trying to authorize()
Check for valid token and refresh it when needed

Handle invalid token

When we have an invalid token but the user previously generated one for
the grading workflow helper we will get an error when trying to create a
new token for them.
travis needs this for the build i think
Store GitHub token in user's home directory

Normalise notebook kernel names

When placing a notebook in the student directory we inspect the kernel
name and re-write names like "Python [conda env:earth-analytics-python]"
to "Python 3". Conda env specific kernels might not be installed on the
student's computers or might have a different name there. This leaves
the instructors notebooks untouched.
